Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AverageCpm
Notes: Average Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).

Name: AveragePosition
Notes: Your ad's position relative to those of other advertisers.

Name: CanManageClients
Notes:
Predicate values / display values:

FALSE / false

Name: ClickType
Enum Values:
URL_CLICKS / Headline
CALLS / Phone calls
OTHER / Other
PRODUCT_EXTENSION_CLICKS / Product plusbox offer
SITELINKS / Sitelink
PRODUCT_LISTING_AD_CLICKS / Product listing ad
GET_DIRECTIONS / Driving direction
OFFER_PRINTS / Print offer
BREADCRUMBS / Breadcrumbs
CALL_TRACKING / Manually dialed phone calls
MOBILE_CALL_TRACKING / Mobile phone calls
LOCATION_EXPANSION / Get location details
UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes:
The Impressions field will reflect how often the ad was served with that click type available. Since ads can serve with multiple click types displayed, impressions may be double counted and the totals may not be accurate.

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

Name: ContentBudgetLostImpressionShare
Notes: The estimated percent of times that your ad was eligible to show on the Display Network but didn't because your budget was too low. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special values "< 10%" or "> 90%".

Name: ContentImpressionShare
Notes: The impressions youâ€™ve received on the Display Network divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special values "< 10%" or "> 90%".

Name: ContentRankLostImpressionShare
Notes: The estimated percentage of impressions on the Display Network that your ads didn't receive due to poor Ad Rank. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special values "< 10%" or "> 90%".

Name: ConversionCategoryName
Notes: Not compatible with non-conversion stats (AverageCpc, Clicks, etc). Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned.  Values: "Other", "View of a key page", "Purchase/Sale", "Signup", "Lead"

Name: ConversionRateManyPerClick
Notes: The number of conversions divided by total clicks that can be tracked to conversions. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: ConversionTypeName
Notes: Not compatible with non-conversion stats (AverageCpc, Clicks, etc).  Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned.

Name: ConversionValue
Notes: The sum of conversion values for all conversions.

Name: ConversionsManyPerClick
Notes: This column reports total conversions, across all the conversion actions you're tracking. How you've chosen to count your conversions (unique or all) affects the number shown in this column.

Name: Cost
Notes: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period. Other costs such as cost-per-call aren't included. For a sum of all costs, use the TotalCost column.

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: CustomerDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: EstimatedCrossDeviceConversions
Notes: Conversions from when a customer clicks on an AdWords ad on one device, then converts on a different device or browser. Cross-device conversions are already included in your EstimatedTotalConversions column.

Name: EstimatedTotalConversionRate
Notes: EstimatedTotalConversions divided by total clicks that can be conversion-tracked. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion.

Name: EstimatedTotalConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all of your conversions, including those that are estimated.

Name: EstimatedTotalConversions
Notes: Best estimate of the total number of conversions that AdWords drives. Includes website, cross-device, and phone call conversions.

Name: ExternalCustomerId
Notes: The Customer ID.

Name: HourOfDay
Notes: The hour of day as a number between 0 and 23, inclusive.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: InvalidClickRate
Notes: The percentage ("x.xx%") of clicks filtered out of your total number of clicks (filtered + non-filtered clicks) during the reporting period.

Name: InvalidClicks
Notes: Number of clicks Google considers illegitimate and doesn't charge you for.

Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: SearchBudgetLostImpressionShare
Notes: The estimated percent of times that your ad was eligible to show on the Search Network but didn't because your budget was too low. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special values "< 10%" or "> 90%"

Name: SearchExactMatchImpressionShare
Notes: The impressions you've received divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive on the Search Network for search terms that matched your keywords exactly (or were close variants of your keyword). A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special values "< 10%" or "> 90%". Not compatible with the field ClickType.

Name: SearchImpressionShare
Notes: The impressions youâ€™ve received on the Search Network divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special values "< 10%" or "> 90%". Not compatible with the fields ClickType and HourOfDay on any report. Not compatible with the field Device on the Product Partition Report.

Name: SearchRankLostImpressionShare
Notes: The estimated percentage of impressions on the Search Network that your ads didn't receive due to poor Ad Rank. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special values "< 10%" or "> 90%". Not compatible with the field ClickType.
